Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Instance 1: Constructs Involved: Initiate Recall, Validate Product Batch, include relationship from "Initiate Recall" to "Validate Product Batch"
   Instance 1: Explanation: "Validate Product Batch" is an inclusion use case that is included only by "Initiate Recall." It is not associated with any actor, not included by any other use case, and does not include, extend, generalize, or get extended by any other use case. It represents a sub-step (validating a batch) rather than a complete service observable to an actor. This is functional decomposition — the behavior of validating a product batch should be part of the "Initiate Recall" use case itself.

